				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: PVP?<a name="41132"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 20 04 9:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Get yourself a bag of Crystalized Pumice's. You can click them while running, just like any item. Sure you have your own dispel song, but the pumice dispels lots more. Start by dispelling their buffs and kei. I usually use at least a full pumice per kill.
<br />

<br />
The next step depends on what zone you are in. If you are in a zone with lots of dark blue or harder mobs, charm them and sick them on your mark. Run like h*ll after you sick them on the mark. If you are out of range the mob will still atack your mark when the charm wears off. Do this until they run or die.
<br />

<br />
If there are no mobs in the zone, your best bet is to do driveby chants. If they resist all your chants, try using more pumices on them. If they still resist, you can try draining their mana.
<br />

<br />
Usually you can run off and heal/dispel yourself at your own leisure so even if you cant kill your mark, you can get them to admit defeat and zone.
<br />

<br />
If you have the ancient mez song (I'm not sure what lvl it is), use that. Its virtually unresistable and has no level limits on pvp server. You can mez/manadrain them or just keep them mezzed until you make them shout &quot;I'm a weenie and this bard has schooled me like a young child.&quot;</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
