				<td colspan="2"><span>Mitcheypoo, the only server where training people is legal is on Sullon Zek. None of the other Zek GM's tolerate it. However, I do agree that pvp is unvbalanced, but the good part of this is a lvl 65 bard is one of the best pkers out there.
<br />

<br />
Resolerus, if you are interested in joining a pvp server, give it a try. The only server where you are allowed to take gear from a fallen opponent is Rallos Zek (and you can easily overcome that by augmenting your gear and making it no-drop). Below is a rundown of the pvp servers.
<br />

<br />
Tallon Zek (pvp teams)- coin loot only. play nice rules in effect
<br />

<br />
Vallon Zek (pvp teams)- same as Tallon Zek
<br />

<br />
Rallos Zek (pvp no teams)- Can loot one item per kill. Cannot loot bags, weapons (i think) and certain other slots. Play nice rules in effect.
<br />

<br />
Sullon Zek (pvp deity teams)- coin loot only. Play nice rules are not enforced. Exp loss is given when killed by an opponent within 6 levels (maybe 8 levels)
<br />

<br />
As you can see, there is a nice selection of pvp servers to choose from<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
